	<div align="center" class="main-content">
		<div class="spacer">
	</div><br>			<label class="collapse_ACT" for="_1"><font size="5px">HydG transcriptional activity</font></label>
				<input id="_1" type="checkbox">
				<div class="ACT"><br><ul><li>ZraR ( HydG ) In S. Typhimurium , ZraR is a response-regulator , activated by its sensor kinase ZraS in a zinc-dependent response to envelope stress ( Leonhartsberger et al. , 2001 ; Appia-Ayme et al. , 2012 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27583250" target="_blank">27583250</a>]<br></li>
<li>However , it has yet to be determined what factors serve to activate HydG or whether HydG is involved in the regulation offdhF .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=1885554" target="_blank">1885554</a>]<br></li>
<li>It is also highly likely that anaerobic expression induces the hyaABCDEF operon , and that HyaF can partially compensate for the loss of HydG .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27566174" target="_blank">27566174</a>]<br></li>
<li>This is consistent with our results , since we show that HydG is essential for the production of active Hyd-5 under both low and high O2 conditions .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27566174" target="_blank">27566174</a>]<br></li>
<li>Further study of this protein is suggested by our work , since the precise role of HydG is obviously more complex given that aerobic-growth of the relevant deletion strain yields an incomplete , large subunit-free , hydrogenase product , but processing of both the large and small subunits occurs anaerobically , despite low enzyme activity resulting .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27566174" target="_blank">27566174</a>]<br></li>
				</div></ul><br>
			<label class="collapse_DOM" for="_2"><font size="5px">HydG protein domains</font></label>
				<input id="_2" type="checkbox">
				<div class="DOM"><br><ul><li>leguminosarum HupH [ 20 ] , we would expect HydG to interact with the small subunit of Hyd-5 , performing an important role in FeS cluster insertion into HydA .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27566174" target="_blank">27566174</a>]<br></li>
<li>Conversely , the data surrounding S. enterica HydG , a natural fusion carrying a C-terminal HoxR domain , suggest that this protein , along with the HoxV homologue HydH , would be critical to include when designing systems requiring [ NiFe ] - hydrogenase activity , and inhibition of such assembly proteins would offer a route to disabling Hyd-5 assembly in pathogenic strains of Salmonella .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27566174" target="_blank">27566174</a>]<br></li>
<li>HydG is particularly interesting , as it probably represents an unusual structure compared with previously studied ` ' family proteins .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27566174" target="_blank">27566174</a>]<br></li>
<li>However , unlike these previously studied proteins , HydG is part of the subgroup of architectures which also contain a C-terminal rubredoxin domain ( Figure S4 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27566174" target="_blank">27566174</a>]<br></li>
				</div></ul><br>
			<label class="collapse_EVO" for="_3"><font size="5px">HydG evolution</font></label>
				<input id="_3" type="checkbox">
				<div class="EVO"><br><ul><li>One of these factors , HydG , shows a high degree of homology with the transcriptional activator NtrC from Klebsiella pneumoniae ( 34 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=1885554" target="_blank">1885554</a>]<br></li>
<li>Salmonella enterica HydF and HydG are both predicted to play a role in the maturation of the FeS clustercontaining small subunit and belong to the Pfam family ` HyaE ' ( PF07449 ) and the ` HupH hydrogenase expression protein , C-terminal conserved region ( ) ' family ( PF04809 ) , respectively [ 26 ] .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27566174" target="_blank">27566174</a>]<br></li>
				</div></ul><br>
			<label class="collapse_RP" for="_4"><font size="5px">Processes regulated by HydG</font></label>
				<input id="_4" type="checkbox">
				<div class="RP"><br><ul><li>HydH/HydG has also been designated ZraS/ZraR ( zinc resistance-associated sensor/regu lator ) , as it is involved in zinc tolerance ( 47 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17921269" target="_blank">17921269</a>]<br></li>
<li>Cell envelope stress , osmolarity sensor , affects membrane permeability , nutrient availability and flagellar expression Nitrogen assimilation Zinc/lead efflux Potassium transport , osmolarity sensor OmpR EnvZ Bang et al. ( 2000 ) ; Higashitani et al. ( 1993 ) ; Shin & Park ( 1995 ) Zimmer et al. ( 2000 ) Leonhartsberger et al. ( 2001 ) Polarek et al. ( 1992 ) GlnG HydG KdpE NarP NarL GlnL HydH KdpD NarQ NarX Nitrate - and nitrite-responsive , anaerobic-respiration Nitrate - and nitrite-responsive , anaerobic-respiration Phosphoglycerate transport Mg uptake , peptide resistance , macrophage survival 2 + Inorganic phosphate uptake/production Stewart ( 2003 ) Stewart ( 2003 ) PgtA PhoP PhoB PgtB PhoQ PhoR Niu et al. ( 1995 ) Groisman & Mouslim ( 2006 ) Conlin et al. ( 2001 ) ; Wanner & Latterell ( 1980 ) Gunn ( 2008 ) LPS modification , peptide resistance PmrA RcsB PmrB RcsC YojN RstB SsrA Capsule synthesis in response to peptidoglycan stress Capsule synthesis in response to peptidoglycan stress Iron transport Control of T3SS-2 and effectors Laubacher & Ades ( 2008 ) Laubacher & Ades ( 2008 ) Jeon et al. ( 2008 ) RstA SsrB Cirillo et al. ( 1998 ) ; Geddes et al. ( 2007 ) ; Hensel et al. ( 1998 ) ; Shea et al. ( 1996 ) Winnen et al. ( 2003 ) Baraquet et al. ( 2006 ) Hensel et al. ( 1999 ) Tricarboxylate transport TctD TorR TtrR UhpA QseF TctE TorS TtrS UhpB QseE Trimethylamine N-oxide respiration Tetrathionate respiration Glucose 6-phosphate-transport Epinephrine , phosphate and sulphate sensor Island et al. ( 1992 ) Reading et al. ( 2009 ) Rasko et al. ( 2008 ) Yamamoto et al. ( 2009 ) Pontel & Soncini ( 2009 ) Quorum-sensing and host stress hormone sensing Citrate utilization Copper sensing Chemotaxis QseB CitB CusR CheY QseC CitA CusS CheA Analysis of the draft S. Dublin CT02021853 sequence indicated that two predicted SK genes may be pseudogenes based on frameshift mutations when compared with S. Typhimurium LT2 .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=20656781" target="_blank">20656781</a>]<br></li>
<li>ZraR ( HydG ) In S. Typhimurium , ZraR is a response regulator , activated by its sensor kinase ZraS in a zinc-dependent response to envelope stress ( Leonhartsberger et al. , 2001 ; Appia-Ayme et al. , 2012 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27583250" target="_blank">27583250</a>]<br></li>
<li>HydG is essential for aerobic and anaerobic Hyd‑5 assembly Deletion of the gene hydG had a negative effect on anaerobic whole cell and periplasmic H2 oxidation ( Fig. 2 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27566174" target="_blank">27566174</a>]<br></li>
