			<label class="collapse_TU" for="_6"><font size="5px">Transcription unit regulated by HydG</font></label>
				<input id="_6" type="checkbox">
				<div class="TU"><br><ul><li>Hyd-1 is encoded by the hyaABCDEF operon and homologues of HyaC ( HydC ) , HyaD ( HydD ) , HyaE ( HydF ) and HyaF ( HydG ) are all encoded by the hydABCDEFGHI operon encoding Hyd-5 ( Fig. 1A ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=21827758" target="_blank">21827758</a>]<br></li>
<li>It is also highly likely that anaerobic expression induces the hyaABCDEF operon , and that HyaF can partially compensate for the loss of HydG .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27566174" target="_blank">27566174</a>]<br></li>
